author: @aysada
content: Nick, I’m so glad you were there! Madonna is and will always be the QUEEN. I am 49 years old and would not have made it past 20 without Madonna. I was certain that I’d never be able to be open and honest about who I was without losing my family possibly my friends. Felt like I didn’t have anyone who would love me for who I was. And then Madonna released Vogue and Truth or Dare and I saw her be warm, demanding, and ultimately maternal with her dancers/children all but one of whom were gay and a “ray of light” came into my world carried by my favorite singer who stood up for gays and fought for AIDS research and awareness and gave a gay teen like me a future. Simply and truthfully, Madonna saved my life.
